 31/7/19 Cape Town the morn the AIF Staff Officer and a doctor came off and told us that we could not land owe to influenza on board . This was not true and I knew that the reason was that no berth was avail . But it would never do to tell the troop this or they would want to be sent off in boat . So we said the ship was in quarantin . Galway , our veri good sport offic and one of the men were put off in order to go to local hospit for oper . They were slung over the side on stretcher . It is an exquisit fresh sunni day today and we are at anchor about 1 mile out from the town which line the shore of the bay . It is a good day for visibl and one can read the ship sight . All
